This paper discusses the security model of the Android operating system, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the security model on the overall system architecture and system performance, which could also fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE), operating systems (cs.OS), and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses deliberate deviations from the abstract model, which could also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
